BREAKING: Nigerian Anti-drug Agency, NDLEA Starts Grilling Disgraced Police Officer, Abba Kyari, Other Collaborators
0 Comments
20 Hours Ago “A junior brother to DCP Kyari is a major beneficiary of funds from the Zenith Bank account of Hussaini Ala from where he at different times received various sums totaling N218,120,000. He also received the sum of N44million in multiple transactions from DCP Abba Kyari.” The police had on Monday said it arrested Kyari and four other police officers over drugs deal which got them declared wanted by the National Drugs Law Enforcement Agency. Others arrested alongside Kyari include ACP Sunday Ubuah, ASP Bawa James, Inspector Simon Agrigba, and Inspector John Nuhu, while the fifth suspect, ASP John Umoru, is still at large. They were arrested on Monday for their involvement in an alleged case of criminal conspiracy, discreditable, unethical and unprofessional conduct, official corruption, and tampering with exhibits in a case of illicit drug trafficking involving a perpetual transnational drug cartel, the police said.



