6 Months Ago Deputy Force Public Relations Officer, Olumuyiwa Adejobi, who confirmed their arrest in a statement in Abuja, revealed that they had been handed over to authorities of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA). Adejobi said interim investigations report revealed that two international drug couriers identified as Chibunna Patrick Umeibe and Emeka Alphonsus, were arrested at Akanu Ibiam International Airport, Enugu on the 19th of January, 2022 upon their arrival from Addis Ababa aboard an Ethiopian Airlines flight ET917. He added that the international narcotics cartel involved had strong ties with some officers of the NDLEA at the airport who are allegedly on their pay roll. 